` but the `UserResponseDto` has `is_new_user` AND `profile_complete?`. Wait, `Us
erResponseDto` has `is_new_user` but the shared types `UserResponse` also has `i
s_new_user`. Let me re-check.\n\nActually looking at `shared-types/src/index.ts`
:\n```typescript\nexport interface UserResponse {\n  id: string;\n  phone: strin
g;\n  is_new_user: boolean;\n  profile_complete?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\nAnd `UserR
esponseDto`:\n```typescript\nexport class UserResponseDto {\n  @IsString()\n  id
: string;\n\n  @IsString()\n  phone: string;\n\n  @IsBoolean()\n  is_new_user: b
oolean;\n\n  @IsBoolean()\n  @IsOptional()\n  profile_complete?: boolean;\n}\n``
`\n\nThese match.\n\nBut wait - in `AuthService.getMe()`, the logic is:\n```type
script\nconst isNewUser = !user.profile || !user.profile.isComplete;\n```\n\nThi
s is WRONG! `is_new_user` should indicate whether the user was JUST created (new
registration), not whether their profile is incomplete. A user could have regist
ered a week ago but not completed their profile. They are NOT a new user.\n\nLoo
king at the PRD `v1-auth-login.md`:\n> 返回体中必须包含 `is_new_user: boolean`，
供 Mobile 判断是否为首次注册。\n\nAnd in `auth.service.ts` `login()`:\n```typesc
ript\ntokens.is_new_user = isNew;\n```\nThis is correct for login.\n\nBut in `ge
tMe()`:\n```typescript\nconst isNewUser = !user.profile || !user.profile.isCompl
ete;\n```\nThis is wrong! `is_new_user` in `getMe` should probably return whethe
r the user is new or not, but we don\'t have a `created_at` comparison. Looking 
at the database schema, there\'s no `last_login_at` either (the PRD mentions it 
but it\'s not in the entity).\n\nActually, let me re-read the PRD more carefully
. The `getMe` endpoint is supposed to return the user\'s info including `is_new_
user` and `profile_complete`. In the `UserResponse` shared type, both fields exi
st. But what does `is_new_user` mean in the context of `getMe`?\n\nLooking at `A
uthBloc._onLoginRequested()`:\n```dart\nfinal meData = await _authRepository.get
